  "narrative": "Scenario test of programme OPRES-PROG-2026 as of 2026-07-15 exercised three severe-but-plausible scenarios across two important business services. SC-01 (ransomware on the core payments platform) exceeded the Retail Payments downtime impact tolerance, recovering in 6.0h against a 4h tolerance, with 0.5h of data replay inside the 1h data-loss tolerance; a high-severity lesson on manual DR runbook steps is recorded for the owner. SC-02 (cloud region loss) recovered inside the Online Banking tolerances with margin to spare, and SC-03 (data centre power) recovered inside tolerance but scored below the severe threshold and covered few dependency dimensions. Suggested review disposition: Escalate, driven by the SC-01 tolerance breach and the high-severity lesson. Regulatory reporting and register updates are handled separately by a human via the operational-resilience-reporter workflow. This pack presents test evidence and a suggested disposition for a human reviewer; the resilience conclusion remains a human adjudication.",
